Davido’s lawyer, Bobo Ajudua aka Prince has argued that Wizkid was ‘ripped off’ at the just-concluded 64th Grammy awards following the singer’s loss. Wizkid was nominated in the ‘Best Global Music Performance’ category, recognising new vocal or instrumental Global music recordings.   Annie Idibia’s brother apologies, blames depression…     Patience Ozokwor, Kanayo O. Kanayo, others attend premier of…     Full list of winners at Grammy Awards 2022   He also received a second nomination in the ‘Best Global Music Album’ category for albums containing at least 51% playing time of new vocal or instrumental Global Music recordings. However, the singer lost both nominations as Pakistani Arooj Aftab’s, “Mohabbat” won the ‘Best Global Music Performance’ award while Beninese Angelique Kidjo’s, “Mother Nature”, won the ‘Best Global Music Album’ category. Reacting to the news, Ajudua insisted Big Wiz album, “Essence” was well deserving of a win at the Grammys noting it was a global anthem. “I don’t know much, and don’t speak much on these things, but we ALL KNOW that award belonged to ‘Essence’. They gave the world an ANTHEM”, he tweeted.